resource/Netherlands\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Katy\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 481}, {\"ngram\": \"Marchanthad\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 493}, {\"ngram\": \"a dazzling gold\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 515}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's event\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"opening night\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 553}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's trio\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 569}, {\"ngram\": \"a shot\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 642}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"victory\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 663}, {\"ngram\": \"the previous round\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"a tall order\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 729}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Roy van den Berg, Harrie Lavreysen and Jeffrey Hoogland had already broken the world record en route to the final and did so again on the biggest stage, a ride of 40.949 making them the first team ever to break the 41-second barrier, and delivering gold almost a second clear of the Brits.\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 768, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harrie Lavreysen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\"}, {\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Hoogland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeffrey Hoogland\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Hoogland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Hoogland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Roy van\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 757}, {\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 841}, {\"ngram\": \"route\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 850}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest stage\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"a ride\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 909}, {\"ngram\": \"the 41-second barrier\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"almost a second clear\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1025}, {\"ngram\": \"the Brits\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1038}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, Britain's performance with a new-look team for theseOlympic Gameswill go down as hugely encouraging.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1048, \"end\": 1055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.6765573198501839, \"rank\": 0.4780712899851113, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a new-look team\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"theseOlympic Gameswill\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remarkably, this is the first time since the event was introduced at Sydney 2000 that Britain have gone into an Olympics without at least one of Sir Jason Kenny and Sir Chris Hoy in the team, but Carlin - the sole survivor from the outfit that one silver in Tokyo - appears to be in superb form ahead of bids for medals in both the individual sprint and Keirin.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1218, \"end\": 1229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997369186877, \"rank\": 2.6308137611808355e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney 2000\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1235, \"end\": 1242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.6765573198501839, \"rank\": 0.4780712899851113, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uni